Interface StoringData<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - tset type
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    BatchTLink<T1,T0>, BatchTSet<T>, BatchTupleTSet<K,V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AllGatherTLink, AllReduceTLink, BatchGatherLink, BatchIteratorLink, BatchIteratorLinkWrapper, BatchSingleLink, BatchTLinkImpl, BatchTSetImpl, BatchTupleTSetImpl, CachedTSet, CheckpointedTSet, ComputeTSet, DirectTLink, GatherTLink, JoinTLink, KeyedBatchIteratorLinkWrapper, KeyedCachedTSet, KeyedCheckpointedTSet, KeyedDirectTLink, KeyedGatherTLink, KeyedGatherUngroupedTLink, KeyedPartitionTLink, KeyedPersistedTSet, KeyedReduceTLink, KeyedSourceTSet, KeyedStoredTSet, KeyedTSet, PartitionTLink, PersistedTSet, ReduceTLink, ReplicateTLink, SourceTSet, StoredTSet

    public interface StoringData<T>
    Adds the capability to to store data for TSets.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      StorableTBase<T> cache()
      Runs this TSet and caches the data to an in-memory DataPartition and exposes the data as another TSet.
      StorableTBase<T> lazyCache()
      Performs caching lazily.
      StorableTBase<T> lazyPersist()
      Performs persisting lazily.
      StorableTBase<T> persist()
      Similar to cache, but the data is stored in a disk based DataPartition.

    • Method Detail

      • cache

        StorableTBase<T> cache()
        Runs this TSet and caches the data to an in-memory DataPartition and exposes the data as another TSet.
        Returns:
        Cached TSet

      • lazyCache

        StorableTBase<T> lazyCache()
        Performs caching lazily. i.e. cache operation would only be performed when the TSet is evaluated explicitly.
        Returns:
        Cached TSet

      • persist

        StorableTBase<T> persist()
        Similar to cache, but the data is stored in a disk based DataPartition. This method would also expose the checkpointing ability to TSets.
        Returns:
        Persisted / Checkpointed TSets

      • lazyPersist

        StorableTBase<T> lazyPersist()
        Performs persisting lazily.
        Returns:
        Persisted / Checkpointed TSets
